OL,3,CHottest year on record: 2024 was first
OL,4,Cyear to break 1.5C warming threshold
OL,6,FLast year was the hottest on record
OL,7,Fand the first to breach a key global
OL,8,Fwarming threshold of 1.5C above pre-
OL,9,Findustrial temperatures, scientists
OL,10,Fhave said.
OL,12,FThey say human-driven climate change
OL,13,Fwas the primary cause for these record
OL,14,Ftemperatures, while other factors such
OL,15,Fas the Pacific Ocean's "El Nino"
OL,16,Fweather phenomenon, which raises
OL,17,Fglobal temperatures also had an effect.
