OL,3,CHottest year on record: 2024 was first
OL,4,Cyear to break 1.5C warming threshold
OL,6,FThe EU's Copernicus Climate Change
OL,7,FService (C3S) confirmed previous
OL,8,Fprojections that 2024 was the warmest
OL,9,Fon record globally and the first
OL,10,Fcalendar year that the average
OL,11,Ftemperature exceeded 1.5C above pre-
OL,12,Findustrial levels.
OL,14,FMeanwhile Analysis from the Met
OL,15,FOffice, University of East Anglia and
OL,16,Fthe National Centre for Atmospheric
OL,17,FScience also found 2024 was the
OL,18,Fhottest on record, and "likely" the
OL,19,Ffirst year exceeding 1.5C.
