OL,3,CHottest year on record: 2024 was first
OL,4,Cyear to break 1.5C warming threshold
OL,6,FPursuing efforts to prevent the world
OL,7,Fwarming more than 1.5C above pre-
OL,8,Findustrial temperatures is one of the
OL,9,Fkey commitments of the global Paris
OL,10,Ftreaty which countries agreed to in
OL,11,F2015, in a bid to avert the most
OL,12,Fdangerous impacts of climate change.
OL,14,FThe UK analysis found that the global
OL,15,Faverage temperature in 2024 was 1.53C
OL,16,Fabove the 1850-1900 average, with a
OL,17,Fmargin of error of plus or minus
OL,18,F0.08C, making it likely the first
OL,19,Fcalendar year to exceed 1.5C.
