OL,3,CHottest year on record: 2024 was first
OL,4,Cyear to break 1.5C warming threshold
OL,6,F"However, it does show that the
OL,7,Fheadroom to avoid an exceedance of
OL,8,F1.5C, over a sustained period, is now
OL,9,Fwafer thin."
OL,11,FAccording to the Copernicus analysis,
OL,12,Ftemperatures were an estimated 1.6C
OL,13,Fabove the pre-industrial level of 1850-
OL,14,F1900, and 0.12C above 2023 ` which was
OL,15,Fthe previous hottest year on record.
OL,17,FIt was the warmest year on record for
OL,18,FEurope, with temperatures 1.47C above
OL,19,Fthe average for the 1991-2020
OL,20,Freference period, the figures show.
